Nigeria’s only representative in the 2019 CAF Champions League, Lobi Stars have been handed a tough draw. The Markurdi based outfit will play 2017 Champions, Wydad Casablanca, Horoya SC and Orlando Pirates from South Africa in group C. Group A houses two top Egyptian teams and former champions of the competition in Al Ahly and Ismaily. AS Vita and Asec Mimosa from Cote d’ Ivoire are the two other teams in the group. Tp Mazembe, Mamelodi Sundowns, Platinum FC and Simba SC are drawn in group B. In group D, two teams from Tunisia Esperance and Club Africiane were also paired together. They will face Constantine and Js Soura as well in the group.